						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in a haystack near the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Telugu-Chōḍa Tirukāḷattidēva Chōḍa mahārāja.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka [11]76 (not verifiable). (A.D. 1254-55). In characters of 13th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. States that, when Tirukāḷattidēva having ruled the mortal world, went away to rule over the celestial world (died), his subordinate (name lost) made a gift of the village of Muṟuguḍlu to god Viśvanāthadēva for the merit of his lord.</p>						

						</summary>
